0008|- [HelpText]
0009|#PRINT L1,L2
0010|*prints the lines L1-L2 of the current edit field on a PostScript printer.
0011|- [New]
0012|*There are alternative forms of PRINT for redirecting the output either
0013|*to a PostScript file or to any (non-PostScript) Windows printer.
0014|- [/New]
0015|*Line numbers and the control column are not printed.
0016|*Lines are usually printed as they appear in the edit field and various
0017|*display modes (shadow characters) correspond to certain printing
0018|*modes of the printer.
0019|*Lines with a '-' in the control are not printed, but are providing various
0020|*control information for printing. For example, a line of the form
0021|*      11 - chapter A in FILE3
0022|*specifies a chapter A from the edit file FILE3 to be printed.
0023|*Control lines of various type enable printing of multipage
0024|*reports with page numbers and headers.
0025|*Also pictures made with the PLOT operation can be automatically
0026|*included.
