0180|- [HelpText]
0181|*The page will be automatically changed according to the selected page
0182|*length.
0183|*The user may, however, control page changes by inserting characters
0184|*/,( and ) in the control column. '/' always starts a new page.
0185|*'(' starts and ')' finishes a table or a chapter which should be
0186|*printed on the same page as a whole.
0188|*When PRINT is working, all printable lines are displayed in a temporary
0189|*window below the PRINT line. To monitor the page changes, the user can
0190|*press the '+' key. The process is then interrupted each time when a page
0191|*ends. To continue, any key can be pressed.
0192|*By redirecting the output to a file or to NUL, page changes can be
0193|*checked without waste of paper.
