0337|- [HelpText]
0338|*Control words in brackets given on control lines of PRINT lists:
0340|*[line_spacing(x)]
0341|*selects a line spacing of x Points (x/72 inches). Default is 12.
0342|*[page_length(x)]
0343|*selects a page length of x Points. Default is 780 (suitable for A4 paper).
0344|*[left_margin(x)]
0345|*sets the left margin to x  picas (x/12 inches). Default is 18.
0346|*[margin(x)]
0347|*sets the left margin to x  dmm (10 dmm = 1 mm).
0348|*[COPIES(x)]
0349|*sets the number of copies of each page to x. Default is 1.
0350|*[LANDSCAPE]
0351|*rotates the A4 page 90 degrees and the next lines will be printed from the top
0352|*of the rotated page using the current left margin. The page length is not
0353|*changed automatically, but it can be reselected separately by
0354|*[page_length(528)], for example.
0355|*[PORTRAIT]
0356|*restores the original orientation of the page and the next lines will be printed
0357|*from the top line onwards.
0359|*Control words in PRINT lists (continued):
0361|*[STORE(x)]
0362|*saves the current printing position as a point with a label x. This x can be any
0363|*word. Example: [STORE(start)].
0364|*[JUMP(x)]
0365|*restores the printing position saved by [STORE(x)].
0366|*[POINT(x,y)]
0367|*takes a new printing position with coordinates x,y given in dmm units. The
0368|*origin is the bottom left corner of the page. The left margin is not changed, bu
0369|*it can be redefined when necessary with [margin(x)] where x is given in
0370|*dmm, too.
0371|*[COUNT_OFF]
0372|*breaks counting of lines and thus prevents an automatic page change.
0373|*[COUNT_ON]
0374|*continues line counting from the situation before the last [COUNT_OFF].
0375|*Control words [COUNT_ON] and [COUNT_OFF] are useful in printing text in
0376|*several columns, for example.
0377|*[PRINT_OFF]
0378|*Lines after this control code are skipped in printing until code
0379|*[PRINT_ON] is encountered and printing continues.
0381|*Control words in PRINT lists (continued):
0383|*[GRAY(x)]
0384|*sets value 0<x<1 (from black to white) for the grayness of the background
S   |             < <
0385|*of the text when using the default shadow 5.
0386|*[FOREBACK(x,y)]
0387|*defines both the grayness of text (x) and its background (y).
0388|*This option is used by selecting a shadow character, say I, by
0389|* - shadow I: [FOREBACK(1,0)] [NORMAL]
0390|*In this case I is the same as the default shadow 7 [REVERSE].
0392|*[FONT_SCALING(x,y)]
0393|*rescales the current font by multiplying the width by x and the height by y.
